        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:48AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 948 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Leipsic, or 11 miles north of Ottawa, moving northeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gallup, Deshler, and Hamler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
